# Browserslist — production browser targets for the AlmaMesh PWA.
#
# AlmaMesh runs the Vedic chart engine entirely on-device: Pyodide (WebAssembly)
# in a Web Worker, an installable service-worker PWA, and ES-module Workers. Those
# are hard runtime requirements, so we target only modern evergreen browsers that
# support WASM + service workers + native ES modules. Anything that can't run the
# engine is out of scope — there is no server-rendered fallback to degrade to.
#
# Consumed automatically by autoprefixer (via postcss.config.mjs) and any other
# browserslist-aware tooling. Keeping an explicit list here (rather than relying on
# the implicit `defaults`) makes the support floor reviewable and intentional.

# Evergreen browsers, recent and still-maintained.
last 2 versions
not dead
> 0.3%

# Hard runtime floor: the on-device engine needs these. Browsers lacking any of
# them cannot run AlmaMesh at all, so we never ship legacy fallbacks for them.
supports es6-module
supports wasm
supports serviceworkers

# Never target IE — it has none of the above.
not IE 11
